Anthrax, Kazakhstan
-------------------
Information received on 22 Aug 2011 from Dr Nigmat Khamitovich
Zhakupbaev, Deputy Chairperson, State Inspection, Ministry of
Agriculture, Astana, Kazakhstan

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 30 Jul 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 5 Aug 2011
Report date: 22 Aug 2011
Date submitted to OIE: 22 Aug 2011
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 27 Jul 2010
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory
(advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Location(s): URAL'SK (Komsomol, Dzhanybekskiy)
Total animals affected: Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths /
Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle: 285 / 3 / 3 / 0 / 0
Sheep: 75 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Equidae: 40 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics: Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent
mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible
animals lost*
Cattle: 1.5 percent / 1.5 percent / 100.00 percent / 1.5 percent
Sheep: 0.00 percent / 0.00 percent / ** / 0.00 percent
Equidae: 0.00 percent / 0.00 percent / ** / 0.00 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction
and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Soil-borne infection
(previously infected site)
Epidemiological comments: Swine and camels have also been vaccinated.

Control measures
Measures applied:
Quarantine
Movement control inside the country
Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)
Administrative division: Species / Total Vaccinated / Details
URAL'SK: Cattle / 285 / Inactivated vaccine [If so, 288 were at risk,
not 285. - Mod.MHJ]
Equidae / 40 / Inactivated vaccine
Sheep / 75 / Inactivated vaccine
Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Reference Veterinary Laboratory
(National laboratory)

Tests and results: Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / agar-gel precipitation (AGP) test / 15 Aug 2011 / Positive
Cattle / bacteriological examination / 15 Aug 2011 / Positive
Cattle / Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 15 Aug 2011 / Positive

Laboratory name and type: National Veterinary Laboratory (National
laboratory)
Tests and results: Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / agar-gel precipitation (AGP) test / 5 Aug 2011 / Positive
Cattle / bacteriological examination / 5 Aug 2011 / Positive
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 5 Aug 2011 / Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of Location: See OIE report [Outbreak is in the far west on the
Kazakh/Russian border. - Mod.MHJ].

